&lt;p&gt;The Bhagavad Gita, a sacred Hindu scripture, consists of 18 chapters, each addressing different aspects of life, duty, and spirituality through the dialogue between Arjuna and Krishna on the battlefield of Kurukshetra. If you don&amp;rsquo;t have time to daily read, connect, assimilate, and practice the teachings, then these 18 lines can help you to start with. There is no shortcut in life; don&amp;rsquo;t assume this is all. This is just a starter.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
